## TL;DR: The Elongated Cushion Cut in One Paragraph

An elongated cushion cut diamond is a standard cushion cut with one number changed: the length-to-width ratio pushed past 1.10 so the stone reads longer, narrower, and more like an oval. The GIA certificate does not say "elongated." The price does not reflect a different shape premium. But the face-up appearance — softer edges, more finger-coverage, genuinely oval-like from three feet away — is completely different from a square cushion.

**Contrarian Truth: the elongated cushion is not a separate cut.** GIA grades it as a cushion modified brilliant, the same classification as the 1.00 square version next to it in the search results. The only thing separating a $1,891 cushion from an oval that costs $2,200+ at the same grade is one field on the certificate: measurements. That ratio arbitrage is the whole point.

**Live price snapshot:**
- 1ct natural GIA G-VS1 Cushion Modified Ideal: **[$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 2ct natural GIA F-VVS2 Cushion Modified Ideal: **[$13,679](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29359194?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 3ct natural GIA G-VVS2 Cushion Modified Ideal: **[$32,692](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961123?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 1.5ct lab IGI E-VVS2 Cushion Modified Excellent: **[$1,422](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28961887?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 2ct lab IGI D-VVS1 Cushion Modified Ideal: **[$2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
- 3ct lab GIA D-VVS1 Cushion Modified Ideal: **[$5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**

**→ The best entry point** for an elongated cushion cut diamond that genuinely reads oval on the hand is a [GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal Cushion Modified at $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) paired with a solitaire setting — total ring from approximately $2,700 — before you can get an equivalent oval at that grade for $2,200+ stone alone.

